│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash originates from an assertion in addMask() │
│ that enforces a constraint when ExtendingManyInputs is true: the SubMask must │
│ be larger than the current mask or, if equal, the second half of the existing │
│ mask must be poison elements. This check ensures the logic for reshuffling    │
│ with two input vectors remains consistent.\n\nIn the provided reproducer, the │
│ SLP vectorizer is building shuffle costs for a horizontal reduction and       │
│ eventually calls ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize(), which unconditionally      │
│ calls addMask(CommonMask, ExtMask, /*ExtendingManyInputs=*/true). If there is │
│ only one input vector, ExtMask can be the same size as CommonMask and         │
│ CommonMask's second half may not be poison, violating the assertion.\n\n2.    │
│ Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug log shows the vectorizer analyzing a large    │
│ bundle of zext operations, and later the ShuffleCostEstimator finalization    │
│ path is taken. The stack trace pinpoints addMask being invoked with           │
│ ExtendingManyInputs=true from ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize(). There's no    │
│ guarantee that InVectors.size() == 2 at that moment. If InVectors.size() ==   │
│ 1, the assertion condition \"SubMask with many inputs support must be larger  │
│ than the mask\" can be false, triggering the abort.\n\n3. Root Cause          │
│ Analysis:\nThe unconditional use of ExtendingManyInputs=true in               │
│ ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize() is incorrect. ExtendingManyInputs is a       │
│ special mode that should only be enabled when reshuffling across two input    │
│ vectors. In this reproducer, CommonMask and ExtMask are likely of the same    │
│ size and CommonMask's second half is not poison, but ExtendingManyInputs is   │
│ set to true even though only a single input vector is involved. This violates │
│ the invariant checked in addMask.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nWe need to   │
│ change the call to addMask in ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize() to set         │
│ ExtendingManyInputs based on whether there are actually two input vectors,    │
│ i.e., InVectors.size() == 2.\n\nEdit Point:\n- File:                          │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n- Line: 10924\n- Change:\n   │
│ From:\n    ::addMask(CommonMask, ExtMask, /*ExtendingManyInputs=*/true);\n    │
│ To:\n    ::addMask(CommonMask, ExtMask,                                       │
│ /*ExtendingManyInputs=*/InVectors.size() == 2);\n\nThis ensures the assertion │
│ in addMask is only applied when handling masks for two-input shuffles.\n\n5.  │
│ Conclusion:\nBy gating the ExtendingManyInputs flag on the actual number of   │
│ input vectors, we respect addMask's invariants and avoid the assertion        │
│ failure. This fix aligns the mask reshuffling logic with the intended usage   │
│ and should prevent the crash for the provided reproducer and analogous cases  │
│ where finalize() operates with a single input vector."})                      │
