│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash originates from an assertion in addMask() that enforces a           │
│ constraint when ExtendingManyInputs is true: the SubMask must be larger than  │
│ the current mask or, if equal, the second half of the existing mask must be   │
│ poison elements. This check ensures the logic for reshuffling with two input  │
│ vectors remains consistent.                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ In the provided reproducer, the SLP vectorizer is building shuffle costs for  │
│ a horizontal reduction and eventually calls ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize(), │
│ which unconditionally calls addMask(CommonMask, ExtMask,                      │
│ /*ExtendingManyInputs=*/true). If there is only one input vector, ExtMask can │
│ be the same size as CommonMask and CommonMask's second half may not be        │
│ poison, violating the assertion.                                              │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The debug log shows the vectorizer analyzing a large bundle of zext           │
│ operations, and later the ShuffleCostEstimator finalization path is taken.    │
│ The stack trace pinpoints addMask being invoked with ExtendingManyInputs=true │
│ from ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize(). There's no guarantee that              │
│ InVectors.size() == 2 at that moment. If InVectors.size() == 1, the assertion │
│ condition "SubMask with many inputs support must be larger than the mask" can │
│ be false, triggering the abort.                                               │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ The unconditional use of ExtendingManyInputs=true in                          │
│ ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize() is incorrect. ExtendingManyInputs is a       │
│ special mode that should only be enabled when reshuffling across two input    │
│ vectors. In this reproducer, CommonMask and ExtMask are likely of the same    │
│ size and CommonMask's second half is not poison, but ExtendingManyInputs is   │
│ set to true even though only a single input vector is involved. This violates │
│ the invariant checked in addMask.                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ We need to change the call to addMask in ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize() to  │
│ set ExtendingManyInputs based on whether there are actually two input         │
│ vectors, i.e., InVectors.size() == 2.                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit Point:                                                                   │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                       │
│ - Line: 10924                                                                 │
│ - Change:                                                                     │
│   From:                                                                       │
│     ::addMask(CommonMask, ExtMask, /*ExtendingManyInputs=*/true);             │
│   To:                                                                         │
│     ::addMask(CommonMask, ExtMask, /*ExtendingManyInputs=*/InVectors.size()   │
│ == 2);                                                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ This ensures the assertion in addMask is only applied when handling masks for │
│ two-input shuffles.                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By gating the ExtendingManyInputs flag on the actual number of input vectors, │
│ we respect addMask's invariants and avoid the assertion failure. This fix     │
│ aligns the mask reshuffling logic with the intended usage and should prevent  │
│ the crash for the provided reproducer and analogous cases where finalize()    │
│ operates with a single input vector.                                          │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
