half of the existing mask must be poison elements. This check ensures the logic
for reshuffling with two input vectors remains consistent.\n\nIn the provided
reproducer, the SLP vectorizer is building shuffle costs for a horizontal
reduction and eventually calls ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize(), which
unconditionally calls addMask(CommonMask, ExtMask, /*ExtendingManyInputs=*/true).
If there is only one input vector, ExtMask can be the same size as CommonMask and
CommonMask's second half may not be poison, violating the assertion.\n\n2.
